radiographic_examinations.findings: The imaged lung bases are clear aside from minimal atelectasis. The hepatic, gallbladder, spleen, adrenal glands, pancreas, and kidneys are normal. The abdominal aorta is normal. The retrocecal appendix is dilated measuring up to 12 mm with periappendiceal fat stranding and mucosal hyperemia. No sign of perforation. Adjacent lymph nodes are prominent and reactive. Small amount of free fluid in the pelvis.
